		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform2><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=177382"><span id=Scholar>senyene</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>130 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.22]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>There is an excellent guide on weight restriction and how much at wich lvl here [link=<a href="http://www.monkly-business.com/articles2.asp?ArticleNum=107][/link]" target=_new>http://www.monkly-business.com/articles2.asp?ArticleNum=107][/link]</a><br>Also plenty of other info to be found, but the come back to your question the ac loss does not seem to be proportional to the (over)weight. At your lvl try to be as close to it as possible if a bit over no problem but don't go too high. It's really blancing between atk and ac. Some items can give you such an atk boost and eventual agi boost that despite overweight the gain outweighs the AC-drawback, once you start progressing you will need to tweak it more and more. Currently my monk is in it's lowest weight config 11 stones wich is excellent for soloing but in raidconfig i bring some heavy resist items and a big slow hardhitting 2hander and am at 24 (monk is lvl 55 btw) stones since i'm not supposed to get agro anyway (unless i'm the puller). So there are times that you don't bother about things too much while at other times you'll want to do anything to get best AC/atk ratio. So depending on what you can afford and obtain, don't bother too much about 2-4 stones overweight and fidle around to see the best combinations. <br><br><i><span class=sm>Edited, Tue Jul 13 18:58:55 2004 by senyene</span class=sm></i></p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Senyene, serving karana on in his own realm.<br></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
